1.   A public room or building for gambling and other entertainment. 2.   also   cas·si·no  A card game for two to four players in which cards on the table are matched by cards in the hand. 3.   A summer or country house in Italy. 1.   (Gambling, except Cards) a public building or room in which gaming takes place, esp roulette and card games such as baccarat and chemin de fer 2.   (Card Games) a variant spelling of  cassino    1.   a building or large room used for meetings, dancing, or esp. for professional gambling.     2.   (in Italy) a small country house or lodge.     3.   Also,    cassino.    a card game in which cards that are face up on the table are taken with eligible cards in the hand.